    "course_title": "INTRODUCTION TO PHYSICAL ACTIVITY PROGRAMMING FOR DIVERSE ABILITIES",
    "description": "Focused and rooted on the application of biological, cultural, social, and research-based practices for professional development in promoting physical activity for everyone, especially those with a variety of disabling conditions.  Work as individuals or teams to plan and implement specified physical activities for individuals with diverse abilities in a variety of settings, including the adapted fitness gym, recreational and competitive endeavors and the home-based exercise.",
